cker in inline mocking. If I call mockConstruction(Base.class) with a new Subclass, could that help cover all invocation paths? I need to consider the stack frames involved as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering mocking strategies**\\n\\nNext, I’m thinking about whether to use Sub when the type of Base is not equal to Sub. If Base is assignable from Sub, that returns true and would cover line 70. I can try `mockConstruction(Greeter.class)` with a new instance of Greeter—this approach seems solid.\\n\\nIf inline construction fails with a resource subclass, perhaps I could temporarily remove that resource. But then again, it seems necessary to have a preconfigured subclass artifact for effective class-mocking coverage. I might also need to inspect the Maven setup to check dependencies.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5BIOlau0dzEsOpGS0snzLEBv|fc_0b85f049df43fced016a2ab68562f881969f14e53c5330e756", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/main/extracted/org/mockito/internal/configuration/plugins/PluginInitializer.java", "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 690, "output": 1019, "cacheRead": 38400, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40109, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781184106788, "responseId": "resp_0b85f049df43fced016a2ab66b611c8196842f2abdef318af2"}}
