[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_5BIOlau0dzEsOpGS0snzLEBv|fc_0b85f049df43fced016a2ab68562f881969f14e53c5330e756", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright (c) 2016 Mockito contributors\n * This program is made available under the terms of the MIT License.\n */\npackage org.mockito.internal.configuration.plugins;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Set;\n\nimport org.mockito.internal.util.collections.Iterables;\nimport org.mockito.plugins.PluginSwitch;\n\nclass PluginInitializer {\n\n    private final PluginSwitch pluginSwitch;\n    private final Set<String> alias;\n\n    PluginInitializer(PluginSwitch pluginSwitch, Set<String> alias) {\n        this.pluginSwitch = pluginSwitch;\n        this.alias = alias;\n    }\n\n    /**\n     * Equivalent to {@link java.util.ServiceLoader#load} but without requiring\n     * Java 6 / Android 2.3 (Gingerbread).\n     */\n    public <T> T loadImpl(Class<T> service) {\n        ClassLoader loader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        if (loader == null) {\n            loader = ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader();\n        }\n        Enumeration<URL> resources;\n        try {\n            resources = loader.getResources(\"mockito-extensions/\" + service.getName());\n        } catch (IOException e) {\n            throw new IllegalStateException(\"Failed to load \" + service, e);\n        }\n\n        try {\n            String classOrAlias =\n                    new PluginFinder(pluginSwitch).findPluginClass(Iterables.toIterable(resources));\n            if (classOrAlias != null) {\n                if (alias.contains(classOrAlias)) {\n                    classOrAlias = DefaultMockitoPlugins.getDefaultPluginClass(classOrAlias);\n                }\n                Class<?> pluginClass = loader.loadClass(classOrAlias);\n                Object plugin = pluginClass.getDeclaredConstructor().newInstance();\n                return service.cast(plugin);\n            }\n            return null;\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            throw new IllegalStateException(\n                    \"Failed to load \" + service + \" implementation declared in \" + resources, e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public <T> List<T> loadImpls(Class<T> service) {\n        ClassLoader loader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        if (loader == null) {\n            loader = ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader();\n        }\n        Enumeration<URL> resources;\n        try {\n            resources = loader.getResources(\"mockito-extensions/\" + service.getName());\n        } catch (IOException e) {\n            throw new IllegalStateException(\"Failed to load \" + service, e);\n        }\n\n        try {\n            List<String> classesOrAliases =\n                    new PluginFinder(pluginSwitch)\n                            .findPluginClasses(Iterables.toIterable(resources));\n            List<T> impls = new ArrayList<>();\n            for (String classOrAlias : classesOrAliases) {\n                if (alias.contains(classOrAlias)) {\n                    classOrAlias = DefaultMockitoPlugins.getDefaultPluginClass(classOrAlias);\n                }\n                Class<?> pluginClass = loader.loadClass(classOrAlias);\n                Object plugin = pluginClass.getDeclaredConstructor().newInstance();\n                impls.add(service.cast(plugin));\n            }\n            return impls;\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            throw new IllegalStateException(\n                    \"Failed to load \" + service + \" implementation declared in \" + resources, e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781184133918}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating testing strategy**\n\nI'm contemplating how to improve test coverage. If a direct test isn't possible, I might have to explain why. Should I add a test at all? Since that doesn't seem ideal, I could consider a direct test within the org_mockito package, but there are restrictions involving imports and private APIs. \n\nI wonder if a subclass constructor could trigger the StackWalkerChecker in inline mocking. If I call mockConstruction(Base.class) with a new Subclass, could that help cover all invocation paths? I need to consider the stack frames involved as well.\n\n**Considering mocking strategies**\n\nNext, I’m thinking about whether to use Sub when the type of Base is not equal to Sub. If Base is assignable from Sub, that returns true and would cover line 70. I can try `mockConstruction(Greeter.class)` with a new instance of Greeter—this approach seems solid.\n\nIf inline construction fails with a resource subclass, perhaps I could temporarily remove that resource. But then again, it seems necessary to have a preconfigured subclass artifact for effective class-mocking coverage. I might also need to inspect the Maven setup to check dependencies.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0b85f049df43fced016a2ab66c64d88196a38957adb77ad49b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKraFrqxmy4XneX3UBYQNCrscoLyRFElqspqhveAm5wNk2inTvbktXIbhZgLX7am8-5yaw_Wrx76EXfdGmthZqyN0yjJtncL-gmIPjyEMGOSdjRbZ5fUWVYzm68BM1M1wrus2LvaX2eiBTvVAz-OgRQhvd8kJBoKzhAMGITi1HIX7jBTJe9yU9GVoa1twJiaceqZKtACQ8vun6SG2uCCP5c8qSD9MfdHNhgNWyXnW9Wnr8Y0xqdMA9dCU05uMgVBWyWovqchf8qnTf84_B-1bWdNW8EgUMbVsAmQLJ-rtqajQ4x4P0SmCrM6nqyDIB-Kl_uoS1_PVZXoLekF3zFYLFNYorsKhWB3lFy7H853ItwXUXzxnKOGLnF80T4-p5tld84iQxoMQvXgimpuVWFTai-wdSyGW1UaaUrkgEsVl-JsnwbdEn43N77BF1mzjilIRLrTR64467AZCV_rarbI0foqw3vph6u2nt-L2slTWo-P8dR8TEmeXTCPZWS4Ke99KHOT0601JADHsOJ-4aRb4dZoW95TJ25mVA4Mz2xgxwZ