ight work better. There’s also the ByteBuddy property in `org.gradle.jvmargs`, which could be useful for tests. I need to tidy up the build.gradle style!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FmMHwWZOeGYtB7fZOPCAHOOq|fc_0b85f049df43fced016a2ab72570f881968d9c720c8afaa8b4", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "test {\n    jvmArgs \"-Djdk.attach.allowAttachSelf=true\"\n}\n", "newText": "test {\n    jvmArgs \"-Djdk.attach.allowAttachSelf=true\"\n    jvmArgs \"-Dnet.bytebuddy.experimental=true\"\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 653, "output": 424, "cacheRead": 46592, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47669, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781184280830, "responseId": "resp_0b85f049df43fced016a2ab7198ca48196b07f0bf4d5a0f14a"}}
